			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-460221">
									

<p>Their purpose is to safeguard humanity from these things, which often necessitates that some things be destroyed. I can understand them keeping useless shit like the vending machines around for the sake of comic relief, but a statuette that surprises people doesn't seem to have any sort of value that would justify keeping it around. What's the point?</p>
<p>Why would they waste the manpower keeping an eye on it? The room to house it?</p>
<p>Don't get me wrong, I actually like this concept a lot and the article is well written. But you gotta keep in mind the purpose of this organization.</p>

